7.text: 1) A reflexive pronoun used as an object comes immediately after a verb or preposition.

8.text: e.g. :- Why don’t you sit down and make yourselves comfortable, so that we can start our discussion straightaway?

9.text: I’m sure we can make the English camp a success and be proud of ourselves.

10.text: 2) A reflexive pronoun form can also be used to show the emphasis given by the speaker to a certain noun or pronoun.

11.text: Our art teacher himself designed the invitation for the Chief Guest.

12.text: Our English teacher said that she herself would prepare them.

13.text: Activity 1.3 A) Rearrange the words to form correct sentences to use reflexive

14.text: pronouns as objects. 1. herself/blamed/what/she/for/happened 2. a/ I/ dictionary/ myself /bought 3. of /made /cup /himself/ he/ a /tea 4. a/ circle/ they/ in/ arranged /themselves 5. defended/ the/ dog/against /kitten/ our/ itself

15.text: B) Follow the example and mark with ^ the positions where you can
